The press briefing by Press Secretary Jay Carney on December 17, 2012 covered multiple topics, including gun violence and the fiscal cliff. Carney stated that the President intends to use the power of his office to engage the American people, lawmakers, law enforcement, mental health experts, educators, and others in an effort to prevent future tragedies. He emphasized that addressing gun violence is part of the solution, but not the only solution, and that a complex problem requires a complex solution. Carney also discussed the ongoing negotiations on the fiscal cliff, stating that the President insists on a balanced approach that includes both revenue increases and spending cuts. He emphasized the need to protect the middle class and seniors from bearing the burden of deficit reduction. The briefing also touched on other topics such as the new Japanese Prime Minister and the Benghazi investigation.